    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A period in United States history following the U.S. Civil War and characterized by industrialization, political corruption, globalization, mass immigration, Western expansion, and widespread cultural and artistic activity. Historians generally agree that the Gilded Age lasted from about 1865 to around 1900.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
